  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add padron peppers, salt, chili powder, smoked paprika, ground cumin, and garlic. Stir-fry for about 5 minutes or until peppers start to soften.",
    "Reduce heat to low and continue cooking the peppers for another 5-10 minutes until they are crispy but not mushy.",
    "Serve hot with a side of quinoa or rice."
